<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="talent-n">talent <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'tælənt/    美 /'tælənt/  </p>
<p>[C] &amp; [U]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>天资；才能</strong></h4>
<p>a natural ability to do sth well(gift)：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a <strong>talent show / competition</strong> 
才艺大赛</p></div>

<ul>
<li>talent for (doing) sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He has a natural talent for music. 
他天生就有音乐天赋。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She <strong>showed</strong> a <strong>talent for</strong> acting at an early age.
她在很小的时候就显示出了表演天赋。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>人才；有才能的人：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There’s <strong>a wealth of talent</strong> in English football.
英格兰足球界人才济济。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>talented /'tæləntɪd/ adj   </p></div>